text.section:
No probation or parole officer of the department shall:
Use his office to influence elections, or to influence the political action of any person;
Serve as a member of the campaign committee of any political party;
Interfere with or participate in the preparation for any election, or the conduct thereof at the polling place, or with the election officers while they are performing their duties;
Be in any manner concerned in demanding, soliciting, or receiving any assessments, subscriptions, or contributions, whether voluntary or involuntary, for any political party or candidate.
